oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Andrews Tabernacle CME: front (east) view
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Eatherly, Brad, photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Andrews Tabernacle Christian Methodist Episicopal Church

Color photograph of the front facade of a church with white-washed wooden siding. A double-leafed door sits under a small gabled porch. The church has a stone foundation and a gabled roof. To the right of the church is a small parsonage.
Andrews Tabernacle Christian Methodist Episcopal Church was established in 1897.
